[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating Java identifiers**\n\nI’m looking into why the Java compiler can’t call methods that start with a dollar sign followed by a digit. The grammar allows identifiers to start with either a dollar sign or a letter and can include digits, so something seems off. It could be that javac prohibits synthetic identifiers and might ignore ACC_SYNTHETIC. I think checking for verbose flags could clarify this situation. Let’s see what those flags reveal!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_037a167200394fec016a0013d0645c81949ebec768ded930b7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqABPS-T2bLpruEApkZ9m2bp9ESC2Unw2GcWF-ZWzIoAzqL6eKkInQlBbVcjOK2ITz4YzLLT1HuXV3gnHwcPdZ72tVAjxUHDqDa1GM7AcO_NlAm32wp59f_--P-MzpKAzAd4Ok_lbSr2M9x0JDUFyNA9_Q96Ziwu-LLJkl1VjEkf7-64B6RksVQ201S0CazH8BhMh7IVQ0V5x-l36hLC3BESH0nE8hDY7C1LDVYce1i0qbOb2n9bbxKyUlu_7FDl9I42aGaXk7GpMFGdVrZJLa2-hqXWifGTKhkUHMB-qbeCFl6R54hqSmKGg03IYX-vsYxNBVIYADd2HNi5yKfpmZVMBjvvD67uQGlNY6YUMLr5xlHgbQOcpDbtdleCRfIVaNcRDjka1T6pKCljUkn-6QO-8eKJQQBeePF45ldCPF4e4DT8wcTowEeOfuur4yv-saFtC2fulGC7nz3np6zZ7_rOFVwOoRuUIXqw7rci_BJWUwVPZqnWuA7Zs5jA_omI55tM25-AKj8w2Dc5wIAbhZ6L-Y8pmX3IkPcOsbIvTMVwkKMlqm9Dim9Cg3ZslCpYUMtqcVgu1Z-xvXjhja5NrzVTb30mHZ3Z3rQi0QedT_F6vpAAZ4AALAHLZv5Q4xQO3GNOiHx03iCStFbTBuz1xhdmrBCvriRQbDr3yhrtbH3CpKOYoo6EQo_0-1q9vz-H0gyYEG6ZKrjZi5hPGp40DpftqBlq_VmIxMTcfGoB19Z1wri9fRSS8b2sPMUF5YnXYFR-QjtbyOowxbVQPBeB3hi_a1mmVyT26U9mWHE8mItoctIsxW_RUT1Wmduv8W2dvOX-l2TpCOR-oWWw-gp_ieIrzc9pZhYwKdOB3wmc9z8elKlpOovmHiYZWoHZzTt35qxfumazy5h4K3B0aJJuzAUn2SMedfIjOQRl6G4Fs30sjm5gKsZT0DUY4s6Pu1eL3r56btkXFmhep71QLryjWpwq1K1vGh1PWs6xEtdSq01RT4TB-mg9E-6y2noPEKs1qLWYInhdmYgQV6ZYRf-WKoSF9r5mePe-rb0JASuy2AsaFnui4Zlx5We0kznFp-DPyxg1feDOVGWRzrRSqo3xqo46R2cG5YLEH1lbP3cHBoc71cs6dvt7PtgBL71andUDDFulw_c2rvnletaHUdEkuKeg9-IkdbskcvSDNmNPQsaIeSmpH-dSdb1a4tDbfTJZa55wLOMpqmYgXe-4simN6DA-RtWOfWUdc1MvDH2vfFcMUpaPBJ4wPS_UeOKb_ccSepTkMciHhx